{% call foundations.section("Introduction") -%}

  <p>Navigation helps a user orient themselves and enables them to browse through content or complete a task.</p>

{%- endcall %}


{% call foundations.section("Navigation patterns") -%}

    <p>There are several patterns available, each was designed to serve a specific purpose or solve a user need.</p>

{%- endcall %}

{% call foundations.section("Using navigation") -%}

    <p>When thinking about how to use navigation, consider how a user would interact with each pattern.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Primary</strong> and <strong>Secondary navigation</strong> allow a user to navigate between pages</li>
        <li><strong>Jump links</strong> allow a user to navigate through an entire page of content</li>
        <li><strong>Tabs</strong> and an <strong>Accordion</strong> allow a user to navigate through a fixed area of content</li>
    </ul>

{%- endcall %}

{% call foundations.section("Primary navigation") -%}

    <h3>Component</h3>
    <p><strong>Primary navigation</strong> contains a slot for a logo, menus or links, and slots for utilities that are placed on a black background.</p>

    [alert goes here]

