    <h3>Usage</h3>
    <p>Primary navigation allows a user to move between the most important pages of a website. It is positioned at the top of a page and contains links to the most important content. It is persistent in all environments, meaning that it sticks to the top of a window as a user scrolls. The <strong>only exception</strong> is when Secondary navigation is positioned below it. It is not mandatory to use Primary navigation on every page, but there must be <em>some form of navigation</em> visible to a user at all times, even a logo that lives on its own.</p>

